d coverage**\\n\\nI’m looking at a report indicating issues possibly due to a field not being null at class initialization during build. I wonder if prior reports after our addition, maybe from an external source, provide insight. It seems like getMethod might be covered while forName isn’t, because the class$ call site in line 488 isn’t instrumented. However, Class.forName also has that line. Maybe it's not included in the native config? The class$ method could be executed during the image build, but the coverage report is about runtime.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_7caowtQhY6VBULSTmRKBI0Le|fc_07a6ad5200574dea0169f5683fb2b88195979dcef48644139a", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find metadata/ant/ant/1.6 -type f -maxdepth 3 -print -exec wc -l {} \\; -exec sed -n '1,200p' {} \\;", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6073, "output": 1290, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35011, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777690669298, "responseId": "resp_07a6ad5200574dea0169f5682dbb3c81959d8d1fbad39bc6f3"}}
