ding**\\n\\nI'm contemplating the potential line involving `forceLoadClass` from `AntClassLoader`, which might not support native images. I think it’s regarding custom dependencies that are less intrusive. It raises the question of which approach is more idiomatic compared to what currently exists. I want to ensure the method I choose aligns well with best practices. It's a nuance worth considering as I analyze my options here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_K2DWQo0BauimQpydgEt9yZyR|fc_07a6ad5200574dea0169f56878ebd881959e51d9ec682908f3", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/ZipEntryTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.lang.reflect.Constructor;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\n\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.AntClassLoader;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.Project;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.types.Path;\nimport org.apache.tools.zip.ZipEntry;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\n", "newText": "import java.io.File;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Constructor;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\n\nimport org.apache.tools.zip.ZipEntry;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\n"}, {"oldText": "    void setComprSizeUpdatesCompressedSizeInFreshAntClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            Object entry = newIsolatedZipEntry(\"archive/isolated-member.txt\");\n            Method setComprSize = entry.getClass().getMethod(\"setComprSize\", Long.TYPE);\n            Method getCompressedSize = entry.getClass().getMethod(\"getCompressedSize\");\n\n            setComprSize.invoke(entry, Long.valueOf(8192L));\n\n            assertThat(getCompressedSize.invoke(entry)).isEqualTo(Long.valueOf(8192L));\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Object newIsolatedZipEntry(String name) throws Exception {\n        Project project = new Project();\n        Path classpath = new Path(project, System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\"));\n        AntClassLoader classLoader = new AntClassLoader(project, classpath, false);\n        Class<?> zipEntryClass = classLoader.forceLoadClass(ZipEntry.class.getName());\n        Constructor<?> constructor = zipEntryClass.getConstructor(String.class);\n        return constructor.newInstance(name);\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "    void setComprSizeUpdatesCompressedSizeInFreshClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        try (ChildFirstZipEntryClassLoader classLoader = new ChildFirstZipEntryClassLoader(classPathUrls())) {\n            Object entry = newIsolatedZipEntry(classLoader, \"archive/isolated-member.txt\");\n            Method setComprSize = entry.getClass().getMethod(\"setComprSize\", Long.TYPE);\n            Method getCompressedSize = entry.getClass().getMethod(\"getCompressedSize\");\n\n            setComprSize.invoke(entry, Long.valueOf(8192L));\n\n            assertThat(getCompressedSize.invoke(entry)).isEqualTo(Long.valueOf(8192L));\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Object newIsolatedZipEntry(ClassLoader classLoader, String name) throws Exception {\n        Class<?> zipEntryClass = classLoader.loadClass(ZipEntry.class.getName());\n        Constructor<?> constructor = zipEntryClass.getConstructor(String.class);\n        return constructor.newInstance(name);\n    }\n\n    private static URL[] classPathUrls() throws Exception {\n        String[] classPathEntries = System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\").split(File.pathSeparator);\n        URL[] urls = new URL[classPathEntries.length];\n        for (int index = 0; index < classPathEntries.length; index++) {\n            urls[index] = new File(classPathEntries[index]).toURI().toURL();\n        }\n        return urls;\n    }\n\n    private static final class ChildFirstZipEntryClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\n        private ChildFirstZipEntryClassLoader(URL[] urls) {\n            super(urls, ZipEntryTest.class.getClassLoader());\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\n                Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n                if (loadedClass == null) {\n                    loadedClass = findZipEntryClass(name);\n                }\n                if (loadedClass == null) {\n                    loadedClass = super.loadClass(name, false);\n                }\n                if (resolve) {\n                    resolveClass(loadedClass);\n                }\n                return loadedClass;\n            }\n        }\n\n        private Class<?> findZipEntryClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!ZipEntry.class.getName().equals(name)) {\n                return null;\n            }\n            try {\n                return findClass(name);\n            } catch (ClassNotFoundException notFound) {\n                return null;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 728, "output": 2268, "cacheRead": 39936, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42932, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777690730059, "responseId": "resp_07a6ad5200574dea0169f5686a82b88195b1cea2d657dc13d9"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_K2DWQo0BauimQpydgEt9yZyR|fc_07a6ad5200574dea0169f56878ebd881959e51d9ec682908f3", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/ZipEntryTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "    ...\n  5  * work. If not, see